[10:43] <deoac> I would like to do a string substitution (not a regex substitution) and learn how many substitutions were made.  e.g. `my $s = 'foo';  $s .= subst('o', 'e', :g)` should change `$s` to `fee`.  How do I know that 2 substituitons were made?

[10:52] <lizmat> if the replacement string has a different size than the original, you could deduce it from the difference in string sizes of the modified string vs the original string

[10:53] <deoac> That cant be guaranteed.

[10:54] <lizmat> if they're the same...  well, then you'd need to do a .match

[10:54] <lizmat> m: 'say "foobarbaz".match("o", :g).elems

[10:54] <camelia> rakudo-moar 81ea8224b: OUTPUT: «===SORRY!=== Error while compiling <tmp>␤Unable to parse expression in single quotes; couldn't find final "'" (corresponding starter was at line 1)␤at <tmp>:1␤------> 'say "foobarbaz".match("o", :g).elems<HERE><EOL>␤    expecting any of:␤   …»

[10:54] <lizmat> m: say "foobarbaz".match("o", :g).elems

